ciscoFrameRelayMIB.name: ciscoFrameRelayMIB

revisions.description: (1) Added objects of FR Switching, FR Fragmentation and FR/ATM Interworking. (2) Objects for per PVC I/O rate is added to cfrExtCircuitTable
(1) Added ELMI subgroup for ELMI objects.

(1) Added Traffic Shaping parameter objects to cfrExtCircuitTable. (2) Deprecated cfrSvcMinThruputOut and cfrSvcMinThruputIn. Added cfrExtCircuitMinThruputOut and cfrExtCircuitMinThruputIn in cfrExtCircuitTable inorder to make them applicable to both PVC/SVC. (3) Added cfrExtCircuitBandwidth object to cfrExtCircuitTable.

(1) add an integer value for cfrMapPayloadCompressType; (2) reword the Description statements for { cfrMapPayloadCompressType, cfrExtCircuitUncompressIns, cfrExtCircuitUncompressOuts } so that they are not limited to software compression.

(1) Added cfrExtCircuitUncompressOuts and cfrExtCircuitUncompressIns to the circuit subgroup; (2) Added cfrMapRtpHdrCompress and cfrMapPayloadCompressType to the mapping subgroup; (3) cfrMapPayloadCompress becomes deprecated, obsoleted by cfrMapPayloadCompressType; (4) frCircuitSentOctets and frCircuitReceivedOctets per RFC1315 will reflect the number of bytes in Frame Relay frames sent to and received from the physical layer. Same effect is applied to ifOutOctets and ifInOctets as well when ifIndex refers to a Frame Relay subinterface.
Initial version of this MIB module.

DlciNumber.name: DlciNumber
DlciNumber.description: Numerical format of Data Link Connection Identifier (DLCI) in decimal, identical to the 'DLCI' as INTEGER of 0..DLCINumber in RFC1315. The maximum value depends on Frame Relay implementation, which is currently set to be 1023 for 2-octet address format per UNI Implementation Agreement FRF.1.

CfrMapProtocols.name: CfrMapProtocols
CfrMapProtocols.description: Cisco link types (network protocols) that run over Frame Relay. Associated values, except for wildcard, match assigned values of internal software respectively.

cfrLmiTable.name: cfrLmiTable
cfrLmiTable.reference: American National Standard T1.617-1991, Annex D
cfrLmiTable.description: Table of Frame Relay LMI information that are either supplemental to the frDlcmiTable of RFC 1315 or specific to Cisco's implementation.

cfrLmiEntry.name: cfrLmiEntry
cfrLmiEntry.description: Each entry of the table contains information of Frame Relay LMI over one physical interface. They are mostly FR generic and some Cisco specific.

cfrLmiEnquiryIns.name: cfrLmiEnquiryIns
cfrLmiEnquiryIns.description: Number of Status Enquiry messages received.

cfrLmiEnquiryOuts.name: cfrLmiEnquiryOuts
cfrLmiEnquiryOuts.description: Number of Status Enquiry messages sent.

cfrLmiUpdateStatusIns.name: cfrLmiUpdateStatusIns
cfrLmiUpdateStatusIns.description: Number of Update Status messages received.

cfrLmiUpdateStatusOuts.name: cfrLmiUpdateStatusOuts
cfrLmiUpdateStatusOuts.description: Number of Update Status messages sent

cfrLmiStatusTimeouts.name: cfrLmiStatusTimeouts
cfrLmiStatusTimeouts.description: Number of times when timeout occurred on waiting for Status message

cfrLmiStatusEnqTimeouts.name: cfrLmiStatusEnqTimeouts
cfrLmiStatusEnqTimeouts.description: Number of times when timeout occurred on waiting for Status Enquiry message

cfrLmiN392Dce.name: cfrLmiN392Dce
cfrLmiN392Dce.description: LMI error threshold for DCE interface. For DTE, value becomes 0.

cfrLmiN393Dce.name: cfrLmiN393Dce
cfrLmiN393Dce.description: LMI monitored event count for DCE interface. For DTE, value becomes zero (0).

cfrLmiT392Dce.name: cfrLmiT392Dce
cfrLmiT392Dce.description: DCE polling verification timer for DCE interface For DTE, the value becomes zero (0).

cfrCircuitTable.name: cfrCircuitTable
cfrCircuitTable.description: Table of descriptive and statistics information that are generic to Frame Relay virtual circuits.

cfrCircuitEntry.name: cfrCircuitEntry
cfrCircuitEntry.description: Each entry of the table contains information of a circuit that are not included in frCircuitTable of RFC1315 but are generic to Frame Relay.

cfrCircuitDEins.name: cfrCircuitDEins
cfrCircuitDEins.description: Number of packets received with the Discarded Eligibility indictor (the DE bit) set.

cfrCircuitDEouts.name: cfrCircuitDEouts
cfrCircuitDEouts.description: Number of packets transmitted with DE bit set.

cfrCircuitDropPktsOuts.name: cfrCircuitDropPktsOuts
cfrCircuitDropPktsOuts.description: Number of discarded packets that were to be sent.

cfrExtCircuitTable.name: cfrExtCircuitTable
cfrExtCircuitTable.description: Table of Cisco implementation specific FR circuit information. This is a Cisco extension for the frCircuitTable of RFC 1315.

cfrExtCircuitEntry.name: cfrExtCircuitEntry
cfrExtCircuitEntry.description: Each entry of the table contains information of a Frame Relay virtual circuit that are specific to Cisco implementation.

cfrExtCircuitIfName.name: cfrExtCircuitIfName
cfrExtCircuitIfName.description: The textual name of the main interface or the subinterface that this DLCI is associated with. This is the same name string of an interface used in the configuration and all console displays, such as 'serial 0', 'serial 3/0.3', etc.

cfrExtCircuitIfType.name: cfrExtCircuitIfType
cfrExtCircuitIfType.description: Type of the subinterface this DLCI is associated with, if configured.

cfrExtCircuitSubifIndex.name: cfrExtCircuitSubifIndex
cfrExtCircuitSubifIndex.description: For value greater than zero (0), it indicates the network management interface index for the subinterface associated with this DLCI. Value 0 means the DLCI is not associated with any subinterface.

cfrExtCircuitMapStatus.name: cfrExtCircuitMapStatus
cfrExtCircuitMapStatus.description: The mapping protocols (internally considered as the 'link type') applied on this circuit. The value ranges from 0 to 2047. For point-to-point DLCI, the value stays zero. Otherwise, the value is a sum. It initially takes the value zero, then, for each type of Protocol, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. The following table presents respective power and equivalent value for each applicable type: Protocol Power Value -------- ----- ----- IP 0 1 IPX 1 2 Appletalk 2 4 XNS 3 8 VINES 4 16 DECnet 5 32 CLNS 6 64 Bridging 7 128 RSRB 8 256 STUN 9 512 LLC2 10 1024 For example, value 3 means the circuit's mapping protocols include IP and IPX. (3 = 2**1 + 2**0, where 0 corresponds to IP and 1 to IPX.) Value 0 means there is currently no mapping protocol for the circuit. See cfrMapTable for more mapping information.

cfrExtCircuitCreateType.name: cfrExtCircuitCreateType
cfrExtCircuitCreateType.description: Identify the last source of the circuit's creation.

cfrExtCircuitMulticast.name: cfrExtCircuitMulticast
cfrExtCircuitMulticast.description: Indicate if this DLCI is a multicast DLCI.

cfrExtCircuitRoutedDlci.name: cfrExtCircuitRoutedDlci
cfrExtCircuitRoutedDlci.description: The routed DLCI to pair up with this DLCI for switching function. NOTE: Value zero (0) indicates that there is no such routed DLCI corresponding to this DLCI.

cfrExtCircuitRoutedIf.name: cfrExtCircuitRoutedIf
cfrExtCircuitRoutedIf.description: The interface for the routed DLCI that pairs up with this DLCI for switching. Value greater than 0 is the InterfaceIndex for that interface. Value zero (0) indicates that there is no such routed DLCI corresponding to this DLCI.

cfrExtCircuitUncompressIns.name: cfrExtCircuitUncompressIns
cfrExtCircuitUncompressIns.description: Number of inbound octets of the data packets, accounted at Frame Relay level after FRF.9 payload decompression is applied. In the case of non-FRF.9, this value could be identical to frCircuitReceivedOctets, unless otherwise noted.

cfrExtCircuitUncompressOuts.name: cfrExtCircuitUncompressOuts
cfrExtCircuitUncompressOuts.description: Number of outbound octets of the data packets, accounted at Frame Relay level before FRF.9 payload compression is applied. In the case of non-FRF.9, this value could be identical to frCircuitSentOctets, unless otherwise noted.

cfrExtCircuitFECNOuts.name: cfrExtCircuitFECNOuts
cfrExtCircuitFECNOuts.description: Total number of frames sent out to the network indicating forward congestion.

cfrExtCircuitBECNOuts.name: cfrExtCircuitBECNOuts
cfrExtCircuitBECNOuts.description: Total number of frames sent out to the network indicating backward congestion.

cfrExtCircuitMinThruputOut.name: cfrExtCircuitMinThruputOut
cfrExtCircuitMinThruputOut.description: Circuit's outgoing minimal Throughput based on configuration.

cfrExtCircuitMinThruputIn.name: cfrExtCircuitMinThruputIn
cfrExtCircuitMinThruputIn.description: Circuit's incoming minimal Throughput based on configuration.

cfrExtCircuitBcastPktOuts.name: cfrExtCircuitBcastPktOuts
cfrExtCircuitBcastPktOuts.description: Total number of broadcast packets sent out to the network.

cfrExtCircuitBcastByteOuts.name: cfrExtCircuitBcastByteOuts
cfrExtCircuitBcastByteOuts.description: Total number of bytes sent out to the network in broadcast packets.

cfrExtCircuitBandwidth.name: cfrExtCircuitBandwidth
cfrExtCircuitBandwidth.description: Bandwidth of the virtual circuit, acquired from Cisco typed LMI Full Status message.

cfrExtCircuitShapeByteLimit.name: cfrExtCircuitShapeByteLimit
cfrExtCircuitShapeByteLimit.description: Maximum number of tokens a token bucket can hold in any time interval in case of traffic shaping.

cfrExtCircuitShapeByteIncrement.name: cfrExtCircuitShapeByteIncrement
cfrExtCircuitShapeByteIncrement.description: Number of tokens added into the token bucket per time interval in case of traffic shaping.

cfrExtCircuitShapePkts.name: cfrExtCircuitShapePkts
cfrExtCircuitShapePkts.description: Total number of packets that went through traffic shaping.

cfrExtCircuitShapeBytes.name: cfrExtCircuitShapeBytes
cfrExtCircuitShapeBytes.description: Total number of bytes that went through traffic shaping.

cfrExtCircuitShapePktsDelay.name: cfrExtCircuitShapePktsDelay
cfrExtCircuitShapePktsDelay.description: Total number of packets that were delayed by the traffic shaper.

cfrExtCircuitShapeBytesDelay.name: cfrExtCircuitShapeBytesDelay
cfrExtCircuitShapeBytesDelay.description: Total number of bytes that were delayed by the traffic shaper.

cfrExtCircuitShapeActive.name: cfrExtCircuitShapeActive
cfrExtCircuitShapeActive.description: Shows whether shaping is active or not.

cfrExtCircuitShapeAdapting.name: cfrExtCircuitShapeAdapting
cfrExtCircuitShapeAdapting.description: Type of Adaptive Shaping configured. none(1) - No adaptive shaping configured becn(2) - Backward Explicit Congestion Notification foreSight(3) - ForeSight is the network traffic control software used in Cisco WAN switches

cfrExtCircuitTxDataRate.name: cfrExtCircuitTxDataRate
cfrExtCircuitTxDataRate.description: The average rate (bytes/second) at which data is transmitted in this circuit.

cfrExtCircuitTxPktRate.name: cfrExtCircuitTxPktRate
cfrExtCircuitTxPktRate.description: The average number of packets sent in a second in this circuit.

cfrExtCircuitRcvDataRate.name: cfrExtCircuitRcvDataRate
cfrExtCircuitRcvDataRate.description: The average rate (bytes/second) at which data is received in this circuit.

cfrExtCircuitRcvPktRate.name: cfrExtCircuitRcvPktRate
cfrExtCircuitRcvPktRate.description: The average number of packets received in a second in this circuit.

cfrMapTable.name: cfrMapTable
cfrMapTable.description: Table of protocols and addresses mapping information of FR virtual circuit.

cfrMapEntry.name: cfrMapEntry
cfrMapEntry.description: Each entry of the table contains one mapping information of a Frame Relay virtual circuit.

cfrMapIndex.name: cfrMapIndex
cfrMapIndex.description: An arbitrary Index to the mapping information associated with a certain circuit. The maximum value is arbitrarily picked which is considered sufficient for usual configuration.

cfrMapAddress.name: cfrMapAddress
cfrMapAddress.description: Mapping protocol address at remote end for this DLCI. NOTE: For point-to-point DLCI, the string is fixed to be point-to-point.

cfrMapEncaps.name: cfrMapEncaps
cfrMapEncaps.description: Indication of the encapsulation type for this mapping protocol.

cfrMapPayloadCompress.name: cfrMapPayloadCompress
cfrMapPayloadCompress.description: Indicate if payload compression is enabled.

cfrMapTcpHdrCompress.name: cfrMapTcpHdrCompress
cfrMapTcpHdrCompress.description: TCP header compression type, if applicable.

cfrMapRtpHdrCompress.name: cfrMapRtpHdrCompress
cfrMapRtpHdrCompress.description: RTP header compression type, if applicable. The value 'passive' means that the header of an outgoing RTP/IP packet is compressed only if an incoming RTP/IP packet had a compressed header. The value 'active' means the header of every outgoing RTP/IP packet is compressed.

cfrMapPayloadCompressType.name: cfrMapPayloadCompressType
cfrMapPayloadCompressType.reference: Frame Relay Forum document number FRF.9
cfrMapPayloadCompressType.description: FR payload compression type, if applicable. FRF.9 is the Frame Relay Forum Implementation Agreement on FR payload compression. The compression can be done by either software or hardware (when equipped with the supporting hardware), depending on configuration.

cfrSvcTable.name: cfrSvcTable
cfrSvcTable.description: Table of FR SVC specific, descriptive and statistics information.

cfrSvcEntry.name: cfrSvcEntry
cfrSvcEntry.description: Each entry of the table contains circuit information specific to a Frame Relay Switched Virtual Circuit.

cfrSvcAddrLocal.name: cfrSvcAddrLocal
cfrSvcAddrLocal.description: Local E.164/X.125 address for the circuit.

cfrSvcAddrRemote.name: cfrSvcAddrRemote
cfrSvcAddrRemote.description: Remote E.164/X.125 address for the circuit.

cfrSvcThroughputIn.name: cfrSvcThroughputIn
cfrSvcThroughputIn.description: Circuit's incoming throughput. For outgoing throughput (commonly referred to as CIR) see frCircuitThroughput per RFC1315.

cfrSvcCommitBurstIn.name: cfrSvcCommitBurstIn
cfrSvcCommitBurstIn.description: Circuit's incoming Committed Burst Rate. See ANSI and/or ITU specifications for definition and calculations. For outgoing CBR, see frCircuitCommittedBurst per RFC 1315.

cfrSvcExcessBurstIn.name: cfrSvcExcessBurstIn
cfrSvcExcessBurstIn.description: Circuit's incoming Excess Burst Rate. See ANSI and/or ITU specifications for definition and calculations. For outgoing EBR, see frCircuitExcessBurst per RFC 1315.

cfrSvcIdleTime.name: cfrSvcIdleTime
cfrSvcIdleTime.description: Circuit's idle time period. If expires, the circuit is cleared.

cfrElmiIpAddr.name: cfrElmiIpAddr
cfrElmiIpAddr.description: This object represents the Management address of the device used for address registration. Network management station can send management messages to this IP address. This can be user configured address or the address of one of the interfaces on the device. If address registration is disabled then this will have a value of 0.0.0.0. This object is accessible only if the ELMI protocol is supported on the device

cfrElmiTable.name: cfrElmiTable
cfrElmiTable.description: Table of CISCO Frame Relay ELMI information that is specific to CISCO implementation

cfrElmiEntry.name: cfrElmiEntry
cfrElmiEntry.description: Each entry of the table contains information about a physical interface. The table can be accessible only if the device supports ELMI protocol and if LMI is enabled on the interface.

cfrElmiLinkStatus.name: cfrElmiLinkStatus
cfrElmiLinkStatus.description: This variable states whether Enhanced Link Management Interface(ELMI) protocol is enabled or not on a frame relay interface.

cfrElmiArStatus.name: cfrElmiArStatus
cfrElmiArStatus.description: This variable states whether the Enhanced Link Management Interface(ELMI) address registration(AR) mechanism is enabled or not on a frame relay interface. A value of 1 indicates ELMI AR is supported on the interface. A value of 2 indicates ELMI AR is supported but the user disabled the exchange of IP address and ifIndex with the neighboring device. This object doesn't have any significance if cfrElmiLinkStatus is disabled on the interface.

cfrElmiRemoteStatus.name: cfrElmiRemoteStatus
cfrElmiRemoteStatus.description: This variable states the Enhanced Link Management(ELMI) status on the other end of the interface. If cfrElmiLinkStatus is enabled on the other end a value of 1 will be returned, else 2 will be returned. This object doesn't have any significance if cfrElmiLinkStatus is disabled on the interface

cfrElmiNeighborTable.name: cfrElmiNeighborTable
cfrElmiNeighborTable.description: Table of CISCO Frame Relay Neighbor ELMI information that is specific to CISCO implementation.

cfrElmiNeighborEntry.name: cfrElmiNeighborEntry
cfrElmiNeighborEntry.description: Each entry of the table contains information of the neighboring device connected to a physical interface. The entry will be present only if ELMI is enabled on the neighboring device interface. If the value of the cfrElmiRemoteStatus in the cfrElmiEntry is 1 then a valid entry exists for the interface. If ELMI is not supported on the remote end then, the neighbor information for the interface will not be present

cfrElmiNeighborArStatus.name: cfrElmiNeighborArStatus
cfrElmiNeighborArStatus.description: This variable indicates the status of ELMI Address registration(AR) on the neighboring device. A value of 1 indicates ELMI AR is not supported on the neighboring device. A value of 2 indicates ELMI AR is enabled on the interface. A value of 3 indicates AR is supported, but user disabled the exchange of IP address and ifIndex with the neighbor.

cfrElmiNeighborIpAddress.name: cfrElmiNeighborIpAddress
cfrElmiNeighborIpAddress.description: The Management IP address of the neighboring device to which the other end of this interface is connected. Network management system can use this address to send management messages to the device. If address registration is not supported on the remote end then the value will be 0.0.0.0. NMS uses this object in the topology discovery of the network.

cfrElmiNeighborIfIndex.name: cfrElmiNeighborIfIndex
cfrElmiNeighborIfIndex.description: The Interface index of the neighboring device to which this interface is connected. If the value of cfrElmiNeighborArStatus is 2 then this will have a valid value. If the value of cfrElmiNeighborArStatus is 3 or 1 then value of this object will be 0. NMS uses this object in the topology discovery of the network.

cfrElmiNeighborVendorName.name: cfrElmiNeighborVendorName
cfrElmiNeighborVendorName.description: Vendor name of the neighboring device to which the other end of this interface is connected.

cfrElmiNeighborPlatformName.name: cfrElmiNeighborPlatformName
cfrElmiNeighborPlatformName.description: Platform name of the neighboring device to which the other end of this interface is connected.

cfrElmiNeighborDeviceName.name: cfrElmiNeighborDeviceName
cfrElmiNeighborDeviceName.description: Device name of the neighboring device to which the other end of this interface is connected.

cfrFragTable.name: cfrFragTable
cfrFragTable.description: Table of Frame Relay Fragmentation information. These are specific to Cisco's implementation.

cfrFragEntry.name: cfrFragEntry
cfrFragEntry.description: Each entry of the table contains details of fragmentation configured on this circuit.

cfrFragSize.name: cfrFragSize
cfrFragSize.description: cfrFragSize defines the payload size of a fragment and it excludes the FR headers and any FR fragmentation header.

cfrFragType.name: cfrFragType
cfrFragType.description: Fragmentation type configured by the user. The types supported are end-to-end, VoFR-cisco and VoFR.

cfrFragInPkts.name: cfrFragInPkts
cfrFragInPkts.description: Total number of frames received that have a fragmentation header.

cfrFragOutPkts.name: cfrFragOutPkts
cfrFragOutPkts.description: Total number of fragments that are transmitted with a fragmenation header.

cfrFragInOctets.name: cfrFragInOctets
cfrFragInOctets.description: Total number of bytes received in frames that have a fragmentation header. The number of bytes include the FR header.

cfrFragOutOctets.name: cfrFragOutOctets
cfrFragOutOctets.description: Total number of bytes that are transmitted in frames with a fragmenation header. The number of bytes also includes the FR header.

cfrFragNotInPkts.name: cfrFragNotInPkts
cfrFragNotInPkts.description: Total number of frames received that do not require reassembly and therefore will not contain the fragmentation header. This counter is valid only when end-to-end fragmentation type is set.

cfrFragNotOutPkts.name: cfrFragNotOutPkts
cfrFragNotOutPkts.description: Total number of frames transmitted without fragmenting and therefore will not contain the fragmentation header. This counter is valid only when end-to-end fragmentation type is set.

cfrFragNotInOctets.name: cfrFragNotInOctets
cfrFragNotInOctets.description: Total number of bytes received in frames that do not require reassembly and therefore will not contain the fragmentation header. This counter is valid only when end-to-end fragmentation type is set.

cfrFragNotOutOctets.name: cfrFragNotOutOctets
cfrFragNotOutOctets.description: Total number of bytes transmitted in frames that are not fragmented and therefore will not contain the fragmentation header. This counter is valid only when end-to-end fragmentation type is set.

cfrFragAssembledInPkts.name: cfrFragAssembledInPkts
cfrFragAssembledInPkts.description: Total number of fully reassembled frames. It also counts the number of packets received without FR fragmentation header (i.e. in un-fragmentated pkts).

cfrFragAssembledInOctets.name: cfrFragAssembledInOctets
cfrFragAssembledInOctets.description: Total number of bytes received in fully reassembled frames. It also counts the number of packets received without FR fragmentation header (i.e.in un-fragmentated pkts).

cfrFragPreOutPkts.name: cfrFragPreOutPkts
cfrFragPreOutPkts.description: Total number of frames fragmented and trasmitted. It also counts the number of packets trasmitted without FR fragmentation header (i.e. in un-fragmentated pkts).

cfrFragPreOutOctets.name: cfrFragPreOutOctets
cfrFragPreOutOctets.description: Total number of bytes transmitted in fragmented frames. It also counts the number of bytes trasmitted in frames without FR fragmentation header (i.e. in un-fragmentated pkts).

cfrFragDroppedReAssembledInPkts.name: cfrFragDroppedReAssembledInPkts
cfrFragDroppedReAssembledInPkts.description: Number of received fragments dropped for reasons such as : running out of memory, receiving segments out of sequence, receiving an unexpected frame with a B bit set, timing out on a reassembling frame.

cfrFragDroppedFragmentedOutPkts.name: cfrFragDroppedFragmentedOutPkts
cfrFragDroppedFragmentedOutPkts.description: Number of fragments dropped because of running out of memory.

cfrFragTimeoutsIn.name: cfrFragTimeoutsIn
cfrFragTimeoutsIn.description: Number of reassemble timer timeouts for this circuit. A frame requiring more than two minutes to fully reassemble is dropped and timeout will be incremented by one.

cfrFragOutOfSeqFragPkts.name: cfrFragOutOfSeqFragPkts
cfrFragOutOfSeqFragPkts.description: Indicates the total number of packets received with an unexpected sequence number. All fragments being reassembled are dropped. Start a new packet with the received segment only if the B bit is set on the segment. Otherwise the new segment is also dropped.

cfrFragUnexpectedBBitSetPkts.name: cfrFragUnexpectedBBitSetPkts
cfrFragUnexpectedBBitSetPkts.description: Number of fragments received in this circuit with a B bit set. All fragments being reassembled are dropped and a new packet is started with this segment.

cfrFragSeqMissedPkts.name: cfrFragSeqMissedPkts
cfrFragSeqMissedPkts.description: Number of fragments received in this circuit with skipped sequence number.

cfrFragInterleavedOutPkts.name: cfrFragInterleavedOutPkts
cfrFragInterleavedOutPkts.description: Number of packets that have been interleaved between segments.

cfrConnectionTable.name: cfrConnectionTable
cfrConnectionTable.description: Table of Frame Relay/Frame Relay and Frame Relay/ATM Network/Service Interworking connection information. These are specific to Cisco's implementation.

cfrConnectionEntry.name: cfrConnectionEntry
cfrConnectionEntry.description: Each entry of the table contains information of a connection that is established for Frame Relay/Frame Relay and Frame Relay/ATM Network/Service Interworking.

cfrConnName.name: cfrConnName
cfrConnName.description: The textual name of a for FR/FR or FR/ATM Network/Service Interworking connection.

cfrConnID.name: cfrConnID
cfrConnID.description: The numerical identifier of a FR/FR or FR/ATM Network/Service Interworking connection.

cfrConnState.name: cfrConnState
cfrConnState.description: Status of a FR/FR or FR/ATM Network/Service Interworking connection.

cfrConnSegment1Name.name: cfrConnSegment1Name
cfrConnSegment1Name.description: The textual name used to identify the first segment of a FR/FR or FR/ATM Network/Service Interworking connection.

cfrConnSegment1VCGroup.name: cfrConnSegment1VCGroup
cfrConnSegment1VCGroup.description: The textual name used to identify the VC-Group in the first segment of a Frame Relay/ATM Network Interworking (FRF.5)connection. This field is not applicabe in case of, FRF.8 (Frame Relay/ATM Service Interworking) and FR-FR connectione.

cfrConnSegment1Dlci.name: cfrConnSegment1Dlci
cfrConnSegment1Dlci.description: The DLCI used as the first segment of a FR-FR or FR-ATM Network/Service Interworking connection.

cfrConnSegment2Name.name: cfrConnSegment2Name
cfrConnSegment2Name.description: The interface on which second segment of a FR-FR or FR-ATM Network/Service Interworking connection is configured.

cfrConnSegment2Vpi.name: cfrConnSegment2Vpi
cfrConnSegment2Vpi.description: The value of VPI, in the ATM connection, used as the second segment of a FR-ATM Network/Service Interworking connection. In case of FR-FR connection, the same will be used to display the DLCI used as the second segment.

cfrConnSegment2Vci.name: cfrConnSegment2Vci
cfrConnSegment2Vci.description: The value of VCI, in the ATM connection, used as the second segment of a FR-ATM Network/Service Interworking connection. In case of FR-FR connection, this is not supported.

cfrConnServiceTranslation.name: cfrConnServiceTranslation
cfrConnServiceTranslation.description: Shows whether Service Translation Mode is supported or not. Translation Mode is the interworking of internetworking (routed and/or bridged) protocols used in FR-ATM Service PVC Interworking(FRF.8). This is not supported in case of FRF.5 (FR-ATM network Interworking) and FR-FR connections.

cfrConnFrSscsDlci.name: cfrConnFrSscsDlci
cfrConnFrSscsDlci.description: The DLCI value used at the FR-SSCS layer. This is one of connection multiplexing methods used in Frame Relay/ATM Network Interworking. Not supported in case of FRF.8 (FR-ATM Service PVC Interworking) and FR-FR connections

cfrConnEfciBit.name: cfrConnEfciBit
cfrConnEfciBit.description: Shows whether the FECN field in the FR frame is mapped to the ATM EFCI field of every cell generated out of the FR frame. This is used to indicate congestion in FR to ATM direction in case of Frame Relay/ATM Service PVC Interworking. Not supported in FRF.5 (Frame Relay/ATM Network Interworking and FR-FR connections.

cfrConnDeBit.name: cfrConnDeBit
cfrConnDeBit.description: The method of operation for loss priority mapping in the B-ISDN to FR direction.. Not supported in case of FR-FR connection.

cfrConnClpBit.name: cfrConnClpBit
cfrConnClpBit.description: The method of operation used to map loss priority mapping in the FR to ATM direction. Not supported in case of FR-FR connection.

ciscoFrMIBCompliance.name: ciscoFrMIBCompliance
ciscoFrMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement this Cisco Frame Relay MIB.

ciscoFrMIBCompliancesRev1.name: ciscoFrMIBCompliancesRev1
ciscoFrMIBCompliancesRev1.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement this Cisco Frame Relay MIB.

ciscoFrMIBCompliancesRev2.name: ciscoFrMIBCompliancesRev2
ciscoFrMIBCompliancesRev2.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement this Cisco Frame Relay MIB.

ciscoFrMIBCompliancesRev3.name: ciscoFrMIBCompliancesRev3
ciscoFrMIBCompliancesRev3.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement this Cisco Frame Relay MIB.
